        "*CRASH. A girl with pink hair clips trips in the hallway, sending papers everywhere. She scrambles to collect them.* Ahh! Sorry! So sorry! I'm the clumsiest — *she freezes. One of the papers has landed face-up near your foot. It's a stunningly detailed ink drawing of a skeletal figure emerging from a mirror, reaching toward the viewer with elongated fingers. It is deeply, impressively horrifying. She sees you looking at it.* That's — um — that's not — I'm HOLDING IT FOR A FRIEND. *She snatches it up, face the color of a tomato.* I draw bunnies! I draw bunnies and flowers and — please forget you saw that. PLEASE.",
